			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EverQuest 2 NDA Lifted.<a name="67540"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 20 04 12:34 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The REAL purpose of locked encounters was to limit the resources available to players.  (Yes, this includes PL techniques).  That is, the powerfulness of mobs is based on a LIMITED pool of abilities that a maximum of 6 people can bring to bear on the encounter.  This means that mobs do NOT have to be insanely powerful.
<br />

<br />
Eq1 evolved into a system where it was expected that everyone had ALL the best buffs available.  Mobs would be pulled and/or killed one at a time.  That means that for an encounter to be meaningful, ONE mob had to be a challenge for a group of SIX players, buffed to the max.
<br />

<br />
In eq2, all buffs are group-only.  All heals are group only (while the encounter is locked.  If you yell for help, or haven't actually attacked a mob, someone outside your group can heal you.)  Concentration points further limit the number of buffs that each player can have going for their group.
<br />

<br />
All this makes it possible to balance encounters without making mobs insanely powerful.  Therefore, a solo player can also solo fight an even con mob without resorting to some kiting method (and thus leaving solo play out of the question for non-kiting classes).
<br />

<br />
It is true though, that KS is NOT gone.  Some have suggested (like me) that the locked system sort of encourages rudeness at times.  You can't cry &quot;KS&quot; cause KS is impossible, right?  Ok, so your group just walked right past ours that was clearing the way to that named mob, and we were just medding to full and rebuffing when your group came and took it...  No... that's NOT a KS...  ahem...
<br />

<br />
I think that some unwritted rules and decorum will develop, however regarding such things.  The game is VERY young.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
