			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EverQuest 2 NDA Lifted.<a name="67868"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 22 04 7:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Currently, every single problem with EQ2 is meaningless when stacked against Server Stability.  If they cannot manage to keep servers and all active zones up and running for 1 full hour(A day would be asking too much at this point), then the launch date is a complete joke, and EQ2 is going go be remembered as another game with high expectations and major disappointments.
<br />

<br />
Performance:
<br />

<br />
Athlong 3100, 1 Gig Ram, Radeon 9600/128 at 4X AGP. - After some recent changes, the game is running fairly smoothly at mid-way graphics settings.  Nothing unreasonable here currently unless you plan to 2-Box on a single system.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Graphics: 
<br />

<br />
Very Shallow.  Visually impressive without hardly any depth whatsoever.  You can see things but you can't climb on them.  Objects exist like the great chains on the side of a bridge, but you fall right through them.  Gone are the days of climbing an object just for the fun of it, or levitating to an area where you aren't &quot;supposed&quot; to be just for fun.  Levitate, of course, does not currently exist.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Character Creation:
<br />

<br />
Alot more limiting than it first appears.  Human females, for example, regardless of how much you change them, still appear like some sort of vampire.   Hairstyles are the only noticable appearance you can change, and many are so awful you end up with the majority of charactors using one or two hairstyles.  Even EQlive has more selection currently, due to at least having different styles of faces for each race.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Tutorial: Blows EQ's Tutorial out of the water.  They really went to the extreme here, the Tutorial is simply amazing.  You can spend several days just enjoying the &quot;Newbie starter zone&quot; called the Isle of Refuge, if you want.  Or you can skip right out of it in 5 minutes.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Will add more later.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">It is true though, that KS is NOT gone. Some have suggested (like me) that the locked system sort of encourages rudeness at times. You can't cry &quot;KS&quot; cause KS is impossible, right? Ok, so your group just walked right past ours that was clearing the way to that named mob, and we were just medding to full and rebuffing when your group came and took it... No... that's NOT a KS... ahem... </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Honestly though, can you really think of a better idea?  Short of exterminating every rude person in the world, which, I think one can safely say, is not a very practical idea, you cannot, by any means, stop this.   Besides, &quot;Medding time&quot; is pretty short in EQ2, it's not like the group is going to have to sit around buffing and medding for 10 minutes like they would in EQ1.  In less than a minute, just about any group would be ready for any encounter they stand a chance against.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
